author: AccessWDUN staff
title: Commerce uses big 1st quarter to rout Towns County
text:
Saturday October 24th, 2015 3:05AM Posted 8:23AM on Saturday 24th October 2015 ( 5 hours from now ) Commerce uses big 1st quarter to rout Towns County By AccessWDUN staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 9: Region titles clinched, set-up in big night of prep football action VIDEO: Red Elephants' whip Jaguars, set up showdown with Loganville 
HIAWASSEE — Commerce used a 35-point first quarter to take control and then cruised to a 49-0 win over Towns County Friday night in Region 8-A action. 
Cole Chancey had a pair of first quarter scores and Trevonta Williford had a 56-yard interception return to highlight the explosion. Will Thomas also a touchdown run and Caleb Brooks connected with Matthew Flint on a touchdown pass in the quarter. 
Austin brook had a touchdown run in the second quarter to give the Tigers (5-3, 4-2 Region 8-A) a 42-0 halftime lead. Nick Patrick added a 76-yard touchdown run in the third quarter. 
The Tigers will play host to George Walton Academy next. Towns County (1-8, 1-6) has now lost six straight. Associated Categories : Sports , High School Sports , Friday Game Night Associated Tags : High school football, Towns County, Commerce football © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
